{"TopicId":168082,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Set EVA Hatch Priority","CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T05:29:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T05:29:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn parts with multiple hatches, like the Mk 3 passenger cabin, it would be nice if there was an option to set a priority for which hatch the Kerbal will go to on EVAs.\u00A0 Alternatively, the menu could give you an \u0022EVA to...\u0022 option and then allow you to select a hatch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI say this because every time I put science instruments near one hatch, and send out a kerbal to reset the experiments or whatever,\u00A0the kerbal will inevitably try to EVA out the \u003Cem\u003Eother \u003C/em\u003Ehatch.\u00A0 I guess I could permanently obstruct the other one with something, but that would a safety hazard.\u00A0 And we can\u0027t have that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flavio hc16","CreatedById":183153,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T08:54:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027m all for this!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"harrisjosh2711","CreatedById":177745,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T09:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t even know you could have two hatches. Cool....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T14:27:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you just click on the hatch and EVA the kerbals that way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eric S","CreatedById":57117,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-01T19:06:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223232446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512138420\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you just click on the hatch and EVA the kerbals that way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s my solution to that problem, so yes it works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-02T05:13:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223232446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512138420\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you just click on the hatch and EVA the kerbals that way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh my goodness, I never knew that was an option. I\u0027ve tried right-clicking on the hatch but it never occurred to me to regular-click it!\u00A0 Thank you kind sir.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn light of that revelation, this is obviously not so important.\u00A0 But still might be nice for those who EVA using the little portraits in the corner.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DualDesertEagle","CreatedById":161533,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-02T09:47:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223233119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512191637\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165625\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aegolius13\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Aegolius13 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut still might be nice for those who EVA using the little portraits in the corner.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEspecially since on vessels with multiple crew compartments it\u0027s easy to have a scientist\u00A0sitting anywhere but in the compartment that has the instruments next to its hatch and EVAing that\u00A0particular scientist sends him out through the hatch of his own compartment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattinoz","CreatedById":118580,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-05T00:43:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223232446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512138420\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/2/2017 at 1:27 AM, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you just click on the hatch and EVA the kerbals that way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven the seat is well ahead of the door does this let you EVA a Kerbal in a MK1 cabin via the MK1 cockpit without making the pilot get out first?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-05T00:56:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you should have both - a hatch priority \u003Cem\u003Ea la \u003C/em\u003Efuel flow assignment, and an \u0022EVA To\u0022 button with a \u0022transfer crew\u0022 like interface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-05T10:31:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223232446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512138420\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 01/12/2017 at 3:27 PM, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you just click on the hatch and EVA the kerbals that way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, i always do that, but its still pretty nice to have the ability to choose the main hatch. So you don\u0027t have to pan and move the camera round for all ya lazy people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T07:13:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223235558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512434621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118580\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mattinoz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 04/12/2017 at 10:43 PM, mattinoz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven the seat is well ahead of the door does this let you EVA a Kerbal in a MK1 cabin via the MK1 cockpit without making the pilot get out first?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in stock.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}